"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-04-10-paris-2024-qualifier-waldrum-lauds-brave-super-falcons-for-securing-olympics-ticket\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Super Falcons head coach, Randy Waldrum has saluted his players after they earned a place at the 2024 Olympic Games.  The West Africans held the Banyana Banyana of South Africa to a 0-0 draw in the second leg of their final qualifying round fixture in Pretoria on Tuesday night.  Waldrum's side secured their passage 1-0 on aggregate.  The American eulogised his players for putting up a good fight in the game.  \\\"The team did everything we asked of them to get the result,\\\" Waldrum said after the game.  \\\"We knew South Africa will come at us, we respect them but this was our seventh or eighth clean sheet, we have been very good defensively  \\\"With time and some proper work, we will also be better on the offensive side, which everyone is asking for.\\\"  Paris 2024: Waldrum demands Euro camp for Super Falcons  EPL: Nothing wrong with their play - Didi Hamann predicts team to win title  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons decamped after postponement  Friendly: Cameroon coach gives reason for defeat to Super Falcons  Friendly: Babajide relishes Super Falcons' win over Cameroon  Friendly: Super Falcons floor Cameroon 3-1 in Yaounde  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"